   By PETER PEARSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
WENTWORTH International Group, led by Mr Robert Gill, has launched legal
proceedings against Mr Haque Khan, former chairman and chief executive, who
left in July.
The USM-quoted plastic packaging products group, whose shares have been
suspended at 3p since October 20 pending its delayed results, has obtained
an injunction against Mr Haque, with the aim of recovering Pounds 1.5m, most
of which relates to the acquisition of Exmapla.
The new board yesterday announced that in the year to March 31 pre-tax
losses came to Pounds 4.05m, against restated profits of Pounds 63,000 or
