The new board is refocusing the group, which is 61.3 per cent owned by an
arm of Banque Indosuez. Edwards, the Belgian corrugated packaging company,
is to be sold and Exmapla is to be closed.
In the six months to September 30 pre-tax losses were Pounds 1.82m on
turnover of Pounds 14.6m after interest charges of Pounds 1.03m.
Losses per share totalled 1.68p.
