<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 92 / Letter: A weighty solution to the problem of red tape
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr SIMON THORNTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, While Charles Batchelor's article on red tape (Growing Business,
December 15) highlights the burden that government bureaucracy places on
small businesses, it misses one crucial point - nobody knows precisely how
big the problem is, or whether the situation is improving or worsening.
To combat this ignorance, an immediate survey should be carried out to
assess the precise costs of understanding and complying with the various
regulations. To gain an accurate picture, it will be essential for all
businesses to provide information. However, if the task is designated to one
of the more customer-oriented government departments, the necessary
questionnaire would run to no more than, say, 50 pages (plus notes, of
course) and would take a maximum of two days for company directors to
complete.
Simon Thornton,
director,
Initiative Europe,
69/71 Broadway, London SW8
</TEXT>
