FT  17 DEC 92 / Water watchdog attacks salaries
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRONWEN MADDOX, Environment Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DIRECTORS' salaries and dividend increases at a water company came under
attack yesterday from one of the customer service committees of Ofwat, the
water industry regulator.
Mr Clive Wilkinson, chairman of the central customer committee, said in a
letter to Mr John Bellak, chairman of Severn Trent, the Birmingham-based
water and sewerage company: 'To see dividend increases at more than twice
the rate of inflation by a monopoly utility at a time of serious recession
is unacceptable.'
Ofwat said yesterday that the committees did not speak on behalf of Mr Ian
Byatt, its director-general.
In July Mr Bellak was given a 29.6 per cent increase in basic salary to
Pounds 160,000. He said last night that total remuneration included bonuses
set at the end of the year, and that because of a cut in bonuses he had seen
a 4 per cent drop in remuneration in the year to March 1992.
