<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 92 / Parliament and Politics: Heseltine warns on coal inquiry
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Michael Heseltine, trade and industry secretary, warned yesterday that
there would be 'uncomfortable conclusions' from his department's inquiry
into the market for coal. He told the Commons employment committee, which is
investigating the proposed closure of 31 pits, that there would be still no
contracts for coal when the existing ones ended in March, apart from a
conditional contract signed by Eastern Electricity and PowerGen this week.
