<DOCNO>FT924-1635</DOCNO>
<PROFILE>_AN-CLQCFABXFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>921217
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 92 / Thorp inquiry completion date
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A GOVERNMENT inquiry into the future of British Nuclear Fuel's Thorp
reprocessing plant at Sellafield in Cumbria may be finished by early
January.
Discussions chaired by the Cabinet Office between the Department of the
Environment, the Ministry of Agriculture, the Treasury and the Foreign
Office, will produce a paper assessing the economic and environmental case
for starting the Pounds 2.8bn plant.
BNF estimates the eventual decommissioning costs of the plant at more than
Pounds 1bn if it starts and becomes radioactive.
