FT  17 DEC 92 / Sluggish recovery in US economy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Moderate increases in industrial production and housing starts, and a
decline in building permits, yesterday offered further evidence of a
sluggish recovery of the US economy, AP-DJ reports from Washington.
Broad-based gains pushed industrial production up a seasonally adjusted 0.4
per cent in November, following a revised 0.5 per cent increase in October,
the Federal Reserve said.
The Commerce Department reported that housing starts rose by 1.5 per cent to
a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.242m units in November. Building
permits fell by 1.5 per cent to a seasonally adjusted rate of 1.122m units.
