have convinced themselves the international community will not stand up to
them and will be forced eventually to recognise the fruits of their
aggression.'
Mr Cyrus Vance and Lord Owen, the co-chairmen of the Geneva peace conference
on the former Yugoslavia, counselled caution on military measures to enforce
the ban on flights and came out firmly against a lifting of the arms embargo
in favour of the Bosnian Moslems.
